1
00:00:02,468 --> 00:00:04,969
[ Ukulele Strumming ]

2
00:00:20,552 --> 00:00:24,155
All right, listen.
You kids are gonna be on your
best behavior right now.

3
00:00:24,157 --> 00:00:27,625
The landlord, Mr. Fischoeder,
is coming over to talk
about the lease,

4
00:00:27,627 --> 00:00:30,094
and we don't know
if he's gonna renew.
He'll renew!

5
00:00:30,096 --> 00:00:32,397
Well, we haven't always
paid our rent on time.

6
00:00:32,399 --> 00:00:34,632
We never pay
our rent on time.
Thanks, Lin.

7
00:00:34,634 --> 00:00:37,635
All right, listen.
Your mother and I are gonna
go make him some food.

8
00:00:37,637 --> 00:00:40,204
That's gonna save us--
our food and our service.

9
00:00:40,206 --> 00:00:42,106
You kids start cleaning now.
Pick that up!

10
00:00:42,108 --> 00:00:44,742
And, Gene, you go outside
and try to drum up
some business.

11
00:00:44,744 --> 00:00:45,810
I'll play
my triangle!

12
00:00:45,812 --> 00:00:47,779
♪ Ding-da-da-ding
da-da-ding, da-da-ding ♪

13
00:00:47,781 --> 00:00:49,647
No!
You don't understand
my music!

14
00:00:49,649 --> 00:00:51,616
Shush. And here's
the other important thing.

15
00:00:51,618 --> 00:00:55,219
When Fischoeder gets here,
you will not-- I repeat, not...

16
00:00:55,221 --> 00:00:57,321
stare at him like he's
some kind of spectacle.

17
00:00:57,323 --> 00:01:00,691
I don't ever stare at him.
I don't know what
you're talking about.

18
00:01:00,693 --> 00:01:04,095
Yes, Mr. Fischoeder
is an eccentric.

19
00:01:04,097 --> 00:01:06,297
Yes, he wears
a white suit.

20
00:01:06,299 --> 00:01:07,331
And an eye patch.

21
00:01:07,333 --> 00:01:08,633
And he drives
a golf cart everywhere.

22
00:01:08,635 --> 00:01:11,636
[ Louise ]
He is one white cat away
from being a super villain.

23
00:01:11,638 --> 00:01:12,637
[ Man ]
Mr. Fischoeder! Aah!

24
00:01:12,639 --> 00:01:14,505
All right, but he
owns this building,
everybody.

25
00:01:14,507 --> 00:01:17,675
He owns the amusement park
and just about everything
else in town,

26
00:01:17,677 --> 00:01:20,378
so you're not
gonna stare at him
when he gets here.

27
00:01:20,380 --> 00:01:23,815
♪ [ Whistling ]
♪ [ Nervous Humming ]

28
00:01:23,817 --> 00:01:26,284
- Here we go!
- Bob, Linda.

29
00:01:26,286 --> 00:01:28,453
Your children are refusing
to acknowledge me.

30
00:01:28,455 --> 00:01:31,322
Uh, kids, stop doing that.
Acknowledge Mr. Fischoeder
right now.

31
00:01:31,324 --> 00:01:33,324
Are you a superhero?
Can I feel your hair?

32
00:01:33,326 --> 00:01:36,194
Stop! Stop!
Go clean something now,
all of you.

33
00:01:36,196 --> 00:01:39,230
So, uh, Mr. Fischoeder,
you know, after all
these years,

34
00:01:39,232 --> 00:01:41,265
I realized you've
never eaten my food.
Mm-hmm.

35
00:01:41,267 --> 00:01:44,135
I want to present to you
one of my favorite
specialty burgers.

36
00:01:44,137 --> 00:01:46,904
Oh, no offense, Bob,
but I have a policy
that I don't dine...

37
00:01:46,906 --> 00:01:48,706
at any of my tenants'
establishments.

38
00:01:48,708 --> 00:01:50,908
Oh. But I saw you eating
at Doucie Sushi.
That's different.

39
00:01:50,910 --> 00:01:56,347
That place is incredible!
Have you had their starfish?
It melts in your mouth.

40
00:01:56,349 --> 00:01:58,216
No? Nobody?

41
00:01:58,218 --> 00:01:59,784
You?
No.

42
00:01:59,786 --> 00:02:02,653
Anyway--
Quiet in here.

43
00:02:02,655 --> 00:02:04,755
Like this a lot, Bob?
Yeah.

44
00:02:04,757 --> 00:02:06,357
Well, I mean,
it's 12:30.

45
00:02:06,359 --> 00:02:09,260
Sorta
the lunch lull.
The lunch lull.

46
00:02:09,262 --> 00:02:10,761
That's what
we call it.
Huh.

47
00:02:10,763 --> 00:02:13,264
Wow. Jimmy Pesto's
lunch lull is really busy.

48
00:02:13,266 --> 00:02:15,466
[ Bob ]
Well, Jimmy Pesto's
is a pizza place--

49
00:02:15,468 --> 00:02:18,369
if you're into that kind
of thing-- pizza.

50
00:02:18,371 --> 00:02:20,371
- [ Chuckles ]
Stupid.
- I like pizza.

51
00:02:20,373 --> 00:02:21,806
Pizza?
Where's pizza?
Shush.

52
00:02:21,808 --> 00:02:26,377
Anyway,
when people want a burger--
a good American burger--

53
00:02:26,379 --> 00:02:27,712
they have nowhere else
to go but--

54
00:02:27,714 --> 00:02:30,848
Sorry. Sorry to interrupt.
Let me be honest with you.

55
00:02:30,850 --> 00:02:34,785
I enjoy you, Bob.
Your mustache--
it's fascinating.

56
00:02:34,787 --> 00:02:36,654
Thank you.
Do you mind if I--

57
00:02:36,656 --> 00:02:38,322
You're touching it.
Yeah. I--

58
00:02:38,324 --> 00:02:40,558
That's--
Yeah, you're--
It's really something.

59
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:42,393
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

60
00:02:42,395 --> 00:02:44,595
[ Moaning ]

61
00:02:44,597 --> 00:02:47,732
Listen,
Jimmy Pesto has tendered
an offer on this space.

62
00:02:47,734 --> 00:02:49,667
Jimmy Pesto?
He wants to move
over here?

63
00:02:49,669 --> 00:02:53,471
Yes, he wants to move
his gift shop over here.
Gift shop?

64
00:02:53,473 --> 00:02:55,606
This would be
an amazing gift shop!

65
00:02:55,608 --> 00:02:58,276
[ Gasps ]
I can do all my Christmas
shopping here!

66
00:02:58,278 --> 00:02:59,477
Yes!
No, no, no,
no, no, no.

67
00:02:59,479 --> 00:03:01,946
Please, I-I think
if you tried my burger,
you'd see that--

68
00:03:01,948 --> 00:03:06,417
Bob, you're always
late with the rent,
and Jimmy pays early.

69
00:03:06,419 --> 00:03:08,452
Wait, wait, wait.
Mr. Fischoeder, please.

70
00:03:08,454 --> 00:03:11,355
Before you make a decision,
just taste my burger.

71
00:03:11,357 --> 00:03:13,724
Just taste it.
[ Sighs ]
Fine.

72
00:03:13,726 --> 00:03:15,226
Another trip to the gym.

73
00:03:15,228 --> 00:03:16,894
Jimmy Pesto may be
a good businessman,
[ Choking ]

74
00:03:16,896 --> 00:03:20,998
but I think you'll find that,
unlike his microwaved junk,
my food is--

75
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:23,501
[ Choking Continues ]
Mr. Fischoeder?

76
00:03:23,503 --> 00:03:24,869
Mr. Fischoeder.

77
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:26,971
[ Gasping ]
He's choking.
He's chok--

78
00:03:26,973 --> 00:03:28,306
How do I do it?
You just push!

79
00:03:28,308 --> 00:03:30,541
- What do I do?
- Push on his belly!
- Hit him in the crotch!

80
00:03:30,543 --> 00:03:33,844
- No, Gene!
Don't hit him in the crotch.
- Yes! Hit him in the crotch!

81
00:03:33,846 --> 00:03:36,581
- I'll hold his hair.
- Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

82
00:03:36,583 --> 00:03:38,449
Linda, please.
Oh, my God!

83
00:03:38,451 --> 00:03:39,550
Wow! He's turning blue!

84
00:03:39,552 --> 00:03:41,986
Put his hand
in warm water!
He can't die!

85
00:03:41,988 --> 00:03:44,455
- He cannot die in here!
- Let's move him outside.

86
00:03:44,457 --> 00:03:47,758
No! Everybody,
hands around him!
Group Heimlich!

87
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:50,528
One, two, three!
Two, three!

88
00:03:50,530 --> 00:03:53,397
- [ All Grunting ]
- [ Bob ] There it is!

89
00:03:53,399 --> 00:03:54,565
- Holy crap!
- God.

90
00:03:54,567 --> 00:03:56,934
Give him
some room, kids.
Give him room!

91
00:03:56,936 --> 00:03:59,370
Oh. Ow.

92
00:03:59,372 --> 00:04:00,605
So, um--
Ow.

93
00:04:00,607 --> 00:04:02,506
Did you, uh--
Did you like it?

94
00:04:02,508 --> 00:04:05,343
[ Groans ]
Your rent is due
Friday night.

95
00:04:05,345 --> 00:04:10,615
And if you're late,
I'm giving your lease
to Jimmy Pesto.

96
00:04:10,617 --> 00:04:12,717
Do you want me
to pack this to go?

97
00:04:12,719 --> 00:04:15,753
You're gonna want
fries with that.

98
00:04:18,724 --> 00:04:20,091
[ Linda ]
So, Mr. Fischoeder's okay.

99
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:23,527
But we've got to
pay the rent in full
by tomorrow night.

100
00:04:23,529 --> 00:04:27,498
Paying the rent in full!
What's next?
Paying your other bills?

101
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:29,567
Don't worry.
We'll figure
something out.

102
00:04:29,569 --> 00:04:32,703
- Right, Bobby?
- Jimmy fricking Pesto.

103
00:04:32,705 --> 00:04:33,638
[ Linda ]
Oh, Bob.

104
00:04:33,640 --> 00:04:36,807
You know,
Pesto's not his real name.
It's Poplopovich.

105
00:04:36,809 --> 00:04:39,076
Of course it is.
The guy's a complete phony.

106
00:04:39,078 --> 00:04:40,778
What is this
obsession with him?

107
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:42,446
I'm not obsessed
with him.
Yeah, you are.

108
00:04:42,448 --> 00:04:46,450
You're both obsessed.
It's like you guys are
stalking each other.

109
00:04:54,526 --> 00:04:56,027
[ No Audible Singing ]

110
00:04:58,397 --> 00:04:59,730
[ Angry Scream ]

111
00:04:59,732 --> 00:05:01,399
I could care less
about the guy.

112
00:05:01,401 --> 00:05:04,335
I think you should both grow up,
at least for the kids' sake.

113
00:05:04,337 --> 00:05:06,771
Let me see.
Let me see.
Ugh. The kids.

114
00:05:06,773 --> 00:05:09,407
Why does Tina have to
like Jimmy Pesto Jr.?

115
00:05:09,409 --> 00:05:11,409
Of all the
13-year-old boys
in the world.

116
00:05:11,411 --> 00:05:14,478
Eh, she likes them too.
It's kind of romantic
though.

117
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:17,715
Two families at war,
a budding romance.

118
00:05:17,717 --> 00:05:19,717
It's like
West Side Story!
[ Groans ]

119
00:05:19,719 --> 00:05:22,553
♪ Du-dun, du-dun
du-dun ♪

120
00:05:22,555 --> 00:05:23,788
Rumble!
Stop.

121
00:05:23,790 --> 00:05:24,555
♪ Dun-dun-dun

122
00:05:24,557 --> 00:05:27,058
You know, Louise is friends
with the twins now too--

123
00:05:27,060 --> 00:05:28,826
Pesto's little boys,
Andy and Ollie.

124
00:05:28,828 --> 00:05:32,530
No, no, no.
I'm calling a ban
on all the Pesto kids.

125
00:05:32,532 --> 00:05:34,732
Our kids are going
to cease contact.

126
00:05:34,734 --> 00:05:37,802
Let's be best friends
forever.
Okay.

127
00:05:38,537 --> 00:05:41,439
Let's cut our hands
and press them together
and become blood brothers!

128
00:05:41,441 --> 00:05:46,010
- Okay! [ Grunting ]
- No, spit brothers! Spit in
your hand and then shake.

129
00:05:46,012 --> 00:05:47,545
Let's do both!
[ Spits ]

130
00:05:47,547 --> 00:05:49,914
Sorry. I'm saving
my spit and blood
for my honeymoon.

131
00:05:49,916 --> 00:05:52,850
Let's rub our eyes together.
You can get my pink eye.

132
00:05:52,852 --> 00:05:56,053
Okay!
[ Both ]
Ow. Ow. Ow. Ow.

133
00:05:56,055 --> 00:05:58,556
Ow. Ooh!
So hard to be friends
these days.

134
00:05:58,558 --> 00:06:01,459
Hey, is that
your brother Jimmy
touching himself all over?

135
00:06:01,461 --> 00:06:02,993
[ Ollie ]
Yeah, he's really
into slow dancing now.

136
00:06:02,995 --> 00:06:06,063
[ Louise ]
He knows it's supposed to be
with other people, right?

137
00:06:06,065 --> 00:06:07,732
It is?
Ugh. Look at Tina.

138
00:06:07,734 --> 00:06:10,801
Kissed the guy,
and she still can't
get his attention.

139
00:06:10,803 --> 00:06:12,703
She should try
pigs in a blanket.

140
00:06:12,705 --> 00:06:15,506
That always
gets my attention.

141
00:06:15,508 --> 00:06:16,507
Ahhh.

142
00:06:16,509 --> 00:06:19,610
♪ [ Ballad, Faint ]
[ Grunts ]

143
00:06:20,812 --> 00:06:24,115
[ Bells Dinging ]
Ugh.
What's he up to now?

144
00:06:24,117 --> 00:06:25,816
What? Oh, my God!

145
00:06:25,818 --> 00:06:28,619
"Now serving burgers."
Burgers!

146
00:06:28,621 --> 00:06:31,689
That's it. It's time
for a showdown.
All right!

147
00:06:31,691 --> 00:06:33,591
♪ We're going to a rumble

148
00:06:33,593 --> 00:06:35,025
I'm gonna confront him.

149
00:06:35,027 --> 00:06:36,093
♪ Gonna confront him

150
00:06:36,095 --> 00:06:37,528
Confront him
right in the face.

151
00:06:37,530 --> 00:06:39,397
♪ Yeah, right
in his handsome face ♪

152
00:06:39,399 --> 00:06:40,231
- What?
- What?

153
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:42,099
You said
"handsome face."
You did.

154
00:06:42,101 --> 00:06:43,734
It's a--
"Right in
his handsome face."

155
00:06:43,736 --> 00:06:45,636
- I know what I said!
- You think he's handsome?

156
00:06:45,638 --> 00:06:47,138
- God, yes.
- No! I'm saying it with anger.

157
00:06:47,140 --> 00:06:52,042
Like, "you handsome face!"
He's so handsome you wanna--
you wanna punch him.

158
00:06:52,044 --> 00:06:53,544
He looks
like Tom Selleck.

159
00:06:53,546 --> 00:06:55,146
When I die,
I want you to cremate me...

160
00:06:55,148 --> 00:06:57,681
and throw my ashes
in Tom Selleck's face.

161
00:06:57,683 --> 00:07:00,217
[ Wheezing Laugh ]
That's a crazy request.

162
00:07:00,219 --> 00:07:02,052
I get it.
All right, let's go.

163
00:07:02,054 --> 00:07:04,188
Kids, watch
the restaurant.

164
00:07:04,489 --> 00:07:06,190
♪ We're going to a rumble

165
00:07:06,192 --> 00:07:09,160
♪ [ Man Singing: Operatic ]
Oh, Lord.

166
00:07:09,162 --> 00:07:10,661
So many people.

167
00:07:10,663 --> 00:07:12,897
Kids, watch
the restaurant.

168
00:07:12,899 --> 00:07:14,598
Tina, watch
the restaurant.

169
00:07:14,600 --> 00:07:17,101
Restaurant, we both know
you can handle this.

170
00:07:17,103 --> 00:07:18,969
Call me if you need me.
Love you.

171
00:07:18,971 --> 00:07:23,107
Jimmy said he'll
be right out. You wanna
try a Pesto-colada?

172
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:24,508
Yeah, sure.
Lin!

173
00:07:24,510 --> 00:07:27,011
What? Free drink.
Yuck. Look at that.

174
00:07:27,013 --> 00:07:28,913
"Pasta la vista, baby"?

175
00:07:28,915 --> 00:07:32,082
"Frank and Zelda
Oldies with Goodies"?
Ugh.

176
00:07:32,084 --> 00:07:35,686
Some confrontation.
I want some action.

177
00:07:35,688 --> 00:07:37,321
I need some action.

178
00:07:37,323 --> 00:07:38,589
[ Gasps ]
There's Jimmy Jr.

179
00:07:38,591 --> 00:07:42,693
[ Sighs ]
Busing tables has never
looked so sensual.

180
00:07:42,695 --> 00:07:44,662
Yet so menial.
[ Tina ]
Yeah.

181
00:07:44,664 --> 00:07:47,832
Here's Jimmy.
Now some fur's gonna fly.

182
00:07:47,834 --> 00:07:50,100
Bob
of Bob's Burgers.

183
00:07:50,102 --> 00:07:53,571
Jimmy so-called Pesto
of Jimmy Pesto's.

184
00:07:53,573 --> 00:07:55,239
Let's skip the niceties,
shall we?

185
00:07:55,241 --> 00:07:57,608
Pesto-colada
for the lady--
on the house.

186
00:07:57,610 --> 00:07:59,977
Thank you.
Except for that nicety.

187
00:07:59,979 --> 00:08:01,779
What are you doing,
Jimmy?
What?

188
00:08:01,781 --> 00:08:03,981
Selling burgers,
coming after my lease.

189
00:08:03,983 --> 00:08:07,818
What are you doing,
Jimmy Poplopovich?

190
00:08:07,820 --> 00:08:08,686
Whoa.
Yeah.

191
00:08:08,688 --> 00:08:12,089
Your name is not
what it says on the--
Mmm. Mmm!

192
00:08:12,091 --> 00:08:14,191
Lin.
Mmm. Yum.

193
00:08:14,193 --> 00:08:15,726
Stop.
That's good.

194
00:08:15,728 --> 00:08:17,261
Bob, I run a business,
all right?

195
00:08:17,263 --> 00:08:20,898
I don't know
what you're doing with
your fancy ingredients.

196
00:08:20,900 --> 00:08:23,000
"I'm Bob,
and I like kale." Kale!

197
00:08:23,002 --> 00:08:24,134
There's nothing wrong
with kale.

198
00:08:24,136 --> 00:08:27,905
Why don't you call it
Snob's Burgers?
Snob's Burgers! Ha!

199
00:08:27,907 --> 00:08:31,809
You think anything that
isn't frozen or rotten
is fancy, Jimmy.

200
00:08:31,811 --> 00:08:34,812
Okay, Mr. Fancy Face.
Let's see who's
got customers.

201
00:08:34,814 --> 00:08:37,248
Ah, da-di-di-di.
Ah, I got some.

202
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:39,683
Let's see who doesn't.
Oh, you.

203
00:08:39,685 --> 00:08:42,753
[ Chuckles ]
I've-- I've got
customers, Jimmy.

204
00:08:42,755 --> 00:08:44,889
They're not there right now.
They have a life.

205
00:08:44,891 --> 00:08:47,591
Oh, yeah?
Well, good luck making rent
by tomorrow night.

206
00:08:47,593 --> 00:08:51,962
Well, good luck trying
to steal my customers
with your Besto-Burger.

207
00:08:51,964 --> 00:08:54,098
They'll never--
Oh, my God!

208
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:55,032
- Bob!
- Unbelievable.

209
00:08:55,034 --> 00:08:57,735
We came to watch
the ball game.
I had the urge to sing Journey!

210
00:08:57,737 --> 00:08:59,303
Come on, Linda.
We're leaving!

211
00:08:59,305 --> 00:09:01,005
Go, go.
Go, go, go, go.

212
00:09:01,007 --> 00:09:02,940
[ Slurping ]

213
00:09:02,942 --> 00:09:05,576
♪ [ Continues ]

214
00:09:07,913 --> 00:09:11,782
Hmm!
You're not gonna get
our lease, Jimmy!

215
00:09:11,784 --> 00:09:14,618
- He's gonna get our lease.
- No, Bobby!

216
00:09:14,620 --> 00:09:16,020
Forget about
Jimmy Pesto.

217
00:09:16,022 --> 00:09:18,389
All we need is one
really good day of business,

218
00:09:18,391 --> 00:09:21,659
and then we can pay our rent
and keep the place, huh?

219
00:09:21,661 --> 00:09:24,194
Huh?
I guess
you're right.

220
00:09:24,196 --> 00:09:27,598
- If we can pack
the house tomorrow.
- Sure! Packed house.

221
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:31,068
We can do that.
Let's have a family
brainstorm right now.

222
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:36,707
Gene, go!
